  "prompt": "Do Jains belong to the OBC category?",
  "response": "The classification of Jain community members as OBC (Other Backward Classes) varies depending on the state and the specific subgroups within the Jain community. In some states of India, certain Jain subgroups may be recognized as OBC based on socio-economic criteria and historical context. However, this classification is not uniform across the entire country, and many Jains are generally considered part of the upper classes and are not listed under the OBC category.\n\nFor accurate and specific information, it is best to refer to the latest notifications and lists issued by the National Commission for Backward Classes (NCBC) or respective state governments, as these classifications can change over time.",
